ght of Innothule, Scourge of the Frogloks, Duke of Ancient Guk.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubludgedredd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bludge Dredd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/3/01 10:29:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   First Bazaar on the server</span><hr size=1> Buying and selling of items has always been an intentional part of the roleplaying vision according to Verant. Now, many people see it as a dirty business and this is primarily due to their resentment of people camping green spawn and whatnot.  <br><br>I know one person who refuses to ever buy anything from another player because they consider it &quot;twinking&quot;.  Even purchasing a jewelers wares is considered twinking and &quot;cheating&quot; to this person because it was not dropped off a mob.  They never sell anything and it just ends up sitting in the bank forever or being given away or destroyed.  Of course, hardly anyone goes to such extremes.  Casting off all materialistic pleasures is a path to enlightenment in certain religions.  It's not the path to pure roleplaying.  <br><br>With that in mind, I really don't see a problem with player run bazaar events and I think Greater Fey will obviously be one of the hotspots due to in being a large city zone with easy access to porting. I fully expect to see numerous people playing full time traders who travel the world as travelling salesmen so to speak.  Where's the harm in that? <br><br>I've seen people stating that the auction channel should be used in character only, but the existence of any  zonewide chat channel is obviously not RP in any way to begin with. The auction channel is by definition an /ooc channel.  If people want to say Buying FBR, I for one won't have an issue with it.  It's a function of the auction channel. <br><br>If you thought that /auction was a mess in E Commons before, with people using abbreviations, just wait till you see 150 people auctioning in 3 sentence descriptions.  You will be hard pressed to even see the item and price before it scrolls off the screen. <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/unumtini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Numtini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/3/01 10:46:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: First Bazaar on the server</span><hr size=1> Buying and selling will be more than necessary. For completing big quests it could end up as ever-auction due to the trivial loot thing.<br><br>I can see people using auctionspeak in a regular auction, like the OOC channel that I would like restored and getting rid of the anonymous/roleplay tags, it's something I grudgingly admit is necessary.<br><br>But if you're going to the trouble to have a bazaar night as a special event. Geez, do it in character. Contact the gnomes and have us bring some fireworks (don't shoot them at the Priest of Discord!). Hand out pies. Have some /duel sparring. Have some races. Have a real medieval style market festival.<br><br>What tweaked me off right away was the uber guild person organizing it and declaring right off that abbreviations were welcome. It's one thing to 